OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
David C. Habiger  Senior Advisor, Silver LakeAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 12 Board Members in 12 different organizations across 18 different industries.See Board Relationships48--
Background

		Mr. David C. Habiger, also known as Dave, has been the Venture Partner of Pritzker Group Venture Capital since June 6, 2013. He is the Founder of Silicon Media Partners. He has been a Senior Advisor at Silver Lake Partners since 2013 and is part of the Value Creation group. Mr. Habiger served as an Advisor at Really Simple Software, Inc. Mr. Habiger served as the Chief Executive Officer of Textura Corporation since August 13, 2015 until 2016 and its Interim Chief Executive ... Officer from April 2015 to August 13, 2015. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of NDS Group Holdings Limited since July 25, 2011 until 2012. From June 2011 to July 2012, he served as Chief Executive Officer of NDS Group Ltd. Mr. Habiger served in various roles at Sonic Solutions, a digital media software company, from 1992 to 2011. Mr. Habiger served as the Chief Executive Officer of Sonic Solutions LLC from September 26, 2005 to 2011 and President from April 28, 2005 to 2011. He served as the Chief Operating officer of Sonic Solutions LLC from April 28, 2005 to September 26, 2005. He joined Sonic Solutions in 1992. He leveraged his 15 year partnership with the Hollywood studios to help move the industry from DVD distribution to internet delivery of movies and TV shows, establishing a leadership role as one of the largest global providers of premium movies and TV shows via the Web and consumer electronic devices. Mr. Habiger served as a Senior Vice President and General Manager at Roxio, from 2002 to 2003 and played a key role in the development of Sonic's OEM and retail markets for consumer software. From 2000 to 2002, he served as a Worldwide Vice President of Sales at Sonic. Mr. Habiger was responsible for the integration of acquisitions, including the Digital Media Division of Veritas and Roxio consumer software group into Sonic. Prior to Sonic, he served as a Product Manager at Roscor Corporation. Mr. Habiger began his career as a founder of Providence Productions. He has been a Director at Enova International, Inc. since October 1, 2014. He has been Independent Director of Tessera Holding Corporation since December 7, 2016. Mr. Habiger has been a Director of Stamps.com Inc. since October 25, 2016 and LiquidPiston, Inc., since July 2013. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board of Backstop Solutions Group, LLC. He serves as a Director of QuickPlay Media Inc. He has been an Independent Director of Control4 Corporation, since September 2012 and its Lead Independent Director since July 2015. He has been an Independent Director of GrubHub Inc. since October 17, 2016. He has been an Independent Director of Akimbo Inc., since September 2007; Echo Global Logistics Inc. since December 28, 2012 and RealD Inc., since July 2011. He served as an Independent Director of Immersion Corporation since September 11, 2014 until June 2, 2017. He served as an Independent Director of DTS Inc, since March 28, 2014 until December 1, 2016 (acquired by Tessera on December 1, 2016). Mr. Habiger served as a Director of NDS Group Holdings Limited since July 1, 2011. He served as a Director of Akimbo Systems, Inc. and Sonic Solutions LLC, from October 2010 to March 2011. He served as a Director of Textura Corporation since December 2012 until 2016. He has been a Member of Advisory Board at 5Barz International Inc. since January 2015. He serves as a Director on numerous public and private Boards, including Silicon Valley Leadership Group, the National Association of Corporate Directors and the Center for Corporate Innovation and the Advisory Board of the University Of Chicago Center for Entrepreneurship. He is a Member of the Academy of Television Arts & Sciences and Society of Motion Picture & Television Engineers. In 2008, he was chosen as one of Corporate Leader Magazine's 40 under 40 business leaders and regularly appears as an industry expert on major media outlets including CNBC, CNN, Fox, The Street.Com and Bloomberg TV. Hollywood Reporter chose him as one of 2010s Digital Power 50 and in 2011, he was chosen as an Ernst & Young Entrepreneur of the Year. Mr. Habiger received an M.B.A. degree from the University of Chicago in 1998 and BBA, a Bachelor's Degree in Business Administration in business media from St. Norbert College in 1991.Read Full Background




